          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, shape",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan and line two baking trays. Mix the {{rolled-oats}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{desiccated-coconut}} and {{soft-brown-sugar}} in a wide bowl. Melt the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{golden-syrup}} in a small pan over a low heat. Stir the {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} into the boiling {{water}}; this is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "bicarb-in-boiling-water",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp999rmv0000u0v4gens40wr"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " step. Stir the bicarb solution into the warm butter-and-syrup; it will foam. Pour into the dry mix and stir to a sticky, even dough. Roll into 20 walnut-sized balls and flatten each on the tray with the palm of your hand to a 6 mm disc, leaving 4 cm between them.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 12 to 15 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 12 to 15 minutes; the biscuits will spread a little and turn deep gold. They will be soft when they come out, that is correct. Cool 5 minutes on the tray, then transfer to a rack. Crisp on the rack as they cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
